      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.sobLlAGQkmWcFBFx]{Magic Hack}</p>\n<p>When you use your @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.uD5oeps79sKG205O]{spellshot} magic hack, you can spend 1 Resolve Point as a part of casting the spell to allow the attack to travel straight to the target, passing through any nonmagical barrier in its way, ignoring hardness and Hit Points (although any magical barrier, such as a <em>@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.spells.Item.dVM22xx7CiYWY8XX]{wall of force}</em>, stops the shot). This ability negates @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.JournalEntry.Kjba2E3Ad5oMJ7hV.JournalEntryPage.1jkwbVTGQihSpCrL]{cover} and @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.JournalEntry.Kjba2E3Ad5oMJ7hV.JournalEntryPage.nyB6pt2dd6iVQGmS]{concealment} modifiers, but otherwise the attack is rolled normally. You must have the spellshot and @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.rEZt5hlJTC9BJj5D]{phase shot} magic hacks to select this magic hack.</p>"
    },
